                            <br/>
                <h3 class="card-title">Alibates Flint Quarries National Monument</h3>
                <br/>
                <p>13,000 years ago, this site was well-known by mammoth hunters as a source of flint for tools. Centuries passed, but the colorful flint never lost its value or usefulness in the Texas Panhandle. Learn how important this site was to the survival, commerce and culture of the people of the High Plains.</p>
                <div class="accordion" id="accordionExample">
